  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Parent Awareness &amp; Communication Training (PACT)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Having a sensory disability can be isolating, and is invariably coupled with the hardships of extreme poverty. Disabled people with sensory impairments often find themselves living life of dependency and segregation. In Northern Malawi, there are few resources available to deaf children and their parents; for example there is only one school for the deaf in the region. Building on a successful pilot project, this project aims to extend services to families with deaf children unable to access education. Developing parents&#x2019; communication skills, awareness and confidence in supporting their children with hearing impairments is seen as the most crucial advance needed to help improve the lives of the children and transform the attitude of their families towards having a deaf child. Facilitators will travel throughout the region, providing educational resources and training for parents and teachers, and encouraging deaf children to participate fully in mainstream school life. Teachers, community leaders and parents will be targeted to improve interaction and inclusion for deaf children inside and outside formal education.</narrative>
  </description>
